{
  "stem": "3341.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But Slovakian fascist government, they knew already.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that was definitely the influence of Germany, when they said, we don't want any Jewish soldiers, because my two brothers were officers in the army.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One of them was in the army about six months, and he was in charge of a small garrison, because they didn't have enough.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They didn't have officer or Sergeant-Majors.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And whoever-- and every Jewish soldier was maybe the best educated and most able.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I-- my father, when they found out I have to-- when I wanted to go to the military service, was terribly angry.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he could have got me out, but I said no.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "If you do anything against it, I will volunteer on my own, because that was still-- we were still part of a Slovakian republic, which was nothing to do-- officially nothing to do-- with Germany.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we didn't know that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I was shipped with the other soldiers to the border of Poland and Slovakia.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we were-- we were then altogether about 400, maybe 500 Jewish boys collected from all the territory of Slovakia.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we were sent there to dig trenches on the mountains.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were to the neck in snow.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "After three weeks doing really-- they treated us like-- we never knew such a treatment before-- like prisoners.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were-- we were down under the-- under the slopes of the mountains.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a big military garrison.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the Jewish soldiers were all concentrated there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were also another group, other barracks.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were in two or three barracks place.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That other barracks had non-Jewish soldiers, and they treated us-- it was the first time how the Jews are treated.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
